    <text id="B0141T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Harris writes to his wife from Danville, stating that he has found a place for
                    the family and will come for them in a few months.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-09-23"><abbr expan="September">Sept.</abbr> 23<hi
                                rend="super">d</hi> '67</date>
                        <name type="place">Danville</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Wife</salute>
                </opener>

                <p> I landed here on Sunday Night at 11 oclock I have seen all of uncle John People.
                    They all send much love to you and say you must certain to come up Christmas you
                    must write soon and let me know how you and the Baby is and you are well or no.
                    I hope you are when I arrived I found all of My People well and hearty I have
                    got a home for you and I will be By after you <orig reg="all">al</orig>
                    <unclear>the end</unclear> of two months for you certain will as I am so tired
                    now I will Bring this to a close your sister was well and sends much love to you
                    so write soon <pb n="2"/>and let me hear from you all tell me whether you or the
                    Baby has been sick or no <orig reg="since">cince</orig> I have been absence good
                    Bye</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>write soon to your affectionate Husband</salute>
                    <signed>James Harris</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
